        "last_activity_date": 1533542616,
        "creation_date": 1533542616,
        "body": "<p>In my experience it is not necessary in any way to use the same product development language as used for CI &amp; CD.<\/p>\n\n<p>By far and away, the <strong>MOST<\/strong> important thing is to allow CI &amp; CD to occur at all.<\/p>\n\n<p>After that, the next most important is for CI &amp; CD to be done as quickly and efficiently as possible.  What languages are used to achieve this aren't critical. Putting it another way; Use whatever languages and tools get the job done as efficiently and effectively as possible.  This applies to the product and the automation used to create the product.<\/p>\n\n<p>For example, I worked on a highly efficient C++ project that used Perl for developing unit tests and Make for executing CI &amp; CD.<\/p>\n",
